243
00:22:14,799 --> 00:22:16,437
And who were all those people?

244
00:22:16,599 --> 00:22:19,591
Don't you see?
It was a ceremony. an initiation.

245
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:21,591
Stop it. Harry.
I know where you're going.

246
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:24,149
It's happened. He's one of them.

247
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:25,753
One of what?

248
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:29,790
Harry is under the impression
Draco Malfoy is now a Death Eater.

249
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,837
You're barking.

250
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,036
What would You-Know-Who
want with Malfoy?

251
00:22:34,199 --> 00:22:38,078
Well. then what's he doing in Borgin
and Burkes? Browsing for furniture?

252
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:40,037
It's a creepy shop. He's a creepy bloke.

253
00:22:40,199 --> 00:22:43,908
Look. his father is a Death Eater.
It only makes sense.

254
00:22:44,079 --> 00:22:45,592
Hermione saw it with her own eyes.

255
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,957
I told you. I don't know what I saw.

256
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,079
I need some air.

257
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:11,749
MAN: Don't worry. When we get
to Hogwarts. we'll sort it out.

258
00:23:26,919 --> 00:23:30,070
[CHATTERING]

259
00:23:31,319 --> 00:23:34,436
DRACO: What was that? Blaise?
BLAISE: Don't know.

260
00:23:34,599 --> 00:23:37,591
PANSY: Relax. boys. It's probably just
a first-year messing around.

261
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:40,991
Come on. Draco. Sit down.
We'll be at Hogwarts soon.

262
00:23:50,279 --> 00:23:53,908
Hogwarts.
What a pathetic excuse for a school.

263
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:55,991
I'd pitch myself off
the Astronomy Tower...

264
00:23:56,159 --> 00:23:58,195
...if I had to continue
for another two years.

265
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,634
What's that supposed to mean?

266
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:04,514
Let's just say you won't see me wasting
my time in Charms class next year.

267
00:24:04,679 --> 00:24:06,078
[BLAISE LAUGHS]

268
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:07,992
Amused. Blaise?

269
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:11,709
We'll see just who's laughing in the end.

270
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:36,555
You two go on.
I wanna check something.

271
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:39,868
Where's Harry?

272
00:24:40,039 --> 00:24:42,872
He's probably already on the platform.
Come on.

273
00:24:57,920 --> 00:25:01,276
DRACO: Didn't Mummy ever tell you
it was rude to eavesdrop. Potter?

274
00:25:01,439 --> 00:25:02,952
Pe trilicus Tu talus .

275
00:25:13,719 --> 00:25:15,118
Oh. yeah...

276
00:25:15,519 --> 00:25:18,670
...she was dead before you could wipe
the drool off your chin.

277
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:26,997
That's for my father.
Enjoy your ride back to London.

278
00:26:09,039 --> 00:26:10,711
Finite.

279
00:26:16,599 --> 00:26:17,827
-He|lo. Harry.
-Luna!

280
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:22,716
-How'd you know where I was?
-Wrackspurts. Your head's full of them.

281
00:26:29,159 --> 00:26:31,719
HARRY: Sorry I made you miss
the carriages. by the way. Luna.

282
00:26:31,879 --> 00:26:34,916
LUNA: That's all right.
It was like being with a friend.

283
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:37,036
Oh. I am your friend. Luna.

284
00:26:37,439 --> 00:26:39,157
That's nice.

285
00:26:39,319 --> 00:26:42,391
About time. I've been looking
all over for you two.

286
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:45,278
Right. Names?

287
00:26:45,519 --> 00:26:47,794
Professor Flitwick.
you've known me for five years.

288
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:49,996
No exceptions. Potter.

289
00:26:50,519 --> 00:26:52,191
Who are those people?

290
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:54,555
Aurors. For security.

291
00:26:54,719 --> 00:26:56,118
What's this cane here. then?

292
00:26:56,399 --> 00:26:58,549
DRACO: It's not a cane. you cretin.
It's a walking stick.

293
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:02,554
FILCH: And what exactly would you
be wanting with a...?

294
00:27:03,679 --> 00:27:06,637
Could be construed
as an offensive weapon.

295
00:27:06,799 --> 00:27:11,827
It's all right. Mr. Filch.
I can vouch for Mr. Malfoy.

296
00:27:18,919 --> 00:27:20,796
DRACO:
Nice face. Potter.

297
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:29,310
Would you like me to fix it for you?

298
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:33,109
Personally. I think you look
a bit more devil-may-care this way...

299
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:34,759
...but it's up to you.

300
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:37,355
Well. have you ever fixed a nose before?

301
00:27:37,519 --> 00:27:41,068
No. but I've done several toes.
and how different are they. really?

302
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:45,834
Um.... Okay. yeah. Give it a go.

303
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:50,116
-Epislrey.
-Ah!

304
00:27:50,279 --> 00:27:51,997
[HARRY GROANING]

305
00:27:55,999 --> 00:27:59,036
-How do I look?
-Exceptiona||y ordinary.

306
00:28:00,119 --> 00:28:01,438
Brilliant.

307
00:28:04,159 --> 00:28:06,070
[CHATTERING]

308
00:28:08,519 --> 00:28:10,475
RON:
Don't worry. He'll be here in a minute.

309
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:16,794
Will you stop eating?

310
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:19,110
Your best friend is missing!

311
00:28:19,279 --> 00:28:22,396
Oi. Turn around. you lunatic.

312
00:28:25,079 --> 00:28:26,512
GINNY:
He's covered in blood again.

313
00:28:27,119 --> 00:28:30,748
-Why is it he's always covered in blood?
-Looks like it's his own this time.

314
00:28:31,199 --> 00:28:32,996
Where have you been?

315
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:35,515
-What happened to your face?
-Later.

316
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:37,238
What've I missed?

317
00:28:37,759 --> 00:28:41,388
Sorting Hat urged us all to be brave
and strong in these troubled times.

318
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:44,950
Easy for it to say. huh?
It's a hat. isn't it?

319
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,118
DUMBLEDORE:
Very best of evenings to you all.

320
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:55,269
HARRY:
Thanks.

321
00:28:57,399 --> 00:29:01,870
First off. let me introduce
the newest member of our staff...

322
00:29:02,039 --> 00:29:04,189
...Horace Slughorn.

323
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:06,635
[STUDENTS APPLAUDING]

324
00:29:07,919 --> 00:29:09,716
Professor Slughorn. I'm happy to say...

325
00:29:09,879 --> 00:29:13,997
...has agreed to resume
his old post as Potions Master.

326
00:29:14,159 --> 00:29:16,957
Meanwhile. the post of
Defense Against the Dark Arts...

327
00:29:17,119 --> 00:29:18,837
...will be taken by Professor Snape.

328
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:20,639
STUDENTS:
Snape?

329
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:22,597
[STUDENTS CLAPPING]

330
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:27,998
DUMBLEDORE:
Now. as you know...

331
00:29:28,159 --> 00:29:31,674
...each and every one of you was searched
upon your arrival here tonight.

332
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:33,751
And you have the right to know why.

333
00:29:34,519 --> 00:29:37,955
Once there was a young man.
who. like you...

334
00:29:38,119 --> 00:29:40,474
...sat in this very hall...

335
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:45,277
...walked this castle's corridors.
slept under its roof.

336
00:29:45,839 --> 00:29:50,037
He seemed to all the world
a student like any other.

337
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,679
His name?

338
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:54,354
Tom Riddle.

339
00:29:54,519 --> 00:29:56,953
[MURMURING]

340
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:00,912
Today. of course...

341
00:30:01,439 --> 00:30:04,636
...he's known all over the world
by another name.

342
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:10,754
Which is why. as I stand looking out
upon you all tonight...

343
00:30:10,919 --> 00:30:13,194
...I'm reminded of a sobering fact.

344
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:17,312
Every day. every hour...

345
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:19,357
...this very minute. perhaps...

346
00:30:19,519 --> 00:30:23,671
...dark forces attempt to penetrate
this castle's walls.

347
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:30,553
But in the end.
their greatest weapon is you.

348
00:30:33,479 --> 00:30:35,515
Just something to think about.

349
00:30:36,719 --> 00:30:38,232
Now. off to bed. Pip-pip.

350
00:30:39,839 --> 00:30:41,557
RON:
That was cheerful.

351
00:30:46,639 --> 00:30:51,190
History of Magic is upstairs.
ladies. not down.

352
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:56,750
Mr. Davies! Mr. Davies!
That is the girls' lavatory.

353
00:30:59,439 --> 00:31:00,792
Potter.

354
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:03,957
Oh. this can't be good.

355
00:31:07,119 --> 00:31:08,438
Enjoying ourselves. are we?

356
00:31:09,319 --> 00:31:12,391
-I had a free period this morning.
-So I noticed.

357
00:31:12,879 --> 00:31:15,188
I would think you would want to
fill it with Potions.

358
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:17,920
Or is it no longer your ambition
to become an Auror?

359
00:31:18,679 --> 00:31:22,149
It was. but I was told I had to
get an “Outstanding“ in my O.W.L.

360
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:25,073
So you did. when Professor Snape
was teaching Potions.

361
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:29,631
However. Professor Slughorn is perfectly
happy to accept N.E.W.T.s students...

362
00:31:29,799 --> 00:31:31,517
...with “ Exceeds Expectations. “

363
00:31:31,999 --> 00:31:33,591
Brilliant. Um....

364
00:31:33,759 --> 00:31:36,114
-Well. I'll head there straightaway.
-Oh. good. good.

365
00:31:36,279 --> 00:31:40,989
Potter. take Weasley with you.
He looks far too happy over there.

366
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:43,948
RON:
I don't wanna take Potions.

367
00:31:44,119 --> 00:31:46,713
This is Ouidditch trials coming up.
I need to practice.

368
00:31:47,919 --> 00:31:49,796
SLUGHORN: Attention to detail
in the preparation...

369
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:52,155
...is the prerequisite of all planning.

370
00:31:53,599 --> 00:31:54,918
Ah.

371
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:58,834
Harry. my boy. I was beginning to worry.
We've brought someone with us. I see.

372
00:31:59,439 --> 00:32:00,588
Ron Weasley. sir.

373
00:32:01,119 --> 00:32:03,474
But I'm dead awful at Potions.
a menace. actually.

374
00:32:03,639 --> 00:32:05,630
-|'m gonna....
SLUGHORN: Nonsense. we'll sort you out.

375
00:32:05,799 --> 00:32:08,757
Any friend of Harry's is a friend of mine.
Get your books out.

376
00:32:08,919 --> 00:32:11,353
HARRY: I haven't actually got
my book yet. and nor has Ron.

377
00:32:11,519 --> 00:32:13,157
Get what you want from the cupboard.

378
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:16,517
Now. as I was saying.
I prepared some concoctions this morning.

379
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:20,468
Any ideas what these might be?

380
00:32:21,919 --> 00:32:24,387
-Yes. Miss...?
-Granger. sir.

381
00:32:27,519 --> 00:32:31,797
That one there is Veritaserum.
It's a truth-telling serum.

382
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:34,554
And that would be Polyjuice Potion.

383
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:39,632
It's terribly tricky to make.

384
00:32:39,799 --> 00:32:41,755
And this is Amortentia...

385
00:32:41,919 --> 00:32:44,228
...the most powerful
love potion in the world.

386
00:32:45,119 --> 00:32:48,794
It's rumored to smell differently to each
person according to what attracts them.

387
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,951
For example. I smell...

388
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:56,559
...freshly mown grass.
and new parchment. and...

389
00:32:56,719 --> 00:32:59,916
...spearmint toothpaste.

390
00:33:01,279 --> 00:33:04,589
SLUGHORN: Amortentia doesn't create
actual love. That would be impossible.

391
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:09,550
But it does cause
a powerful infatuation or obsession.

392
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:16,114
And for that reason. it is probably
the most dangerous potion in this room.

393
00:33:21,439 --> 00:33:24,112
Sir? You haven't told us
what's in that one.

394
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:26,118
Oh. yes.

395
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,748
What you see before you.
ladies and gentlemen...

396
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:34,119
...is a curious little potion
known as Felix Felicis.

397
00:33:34,519 --> 00:33:36,669
But it is more commonly referred to as--

398
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:41,914
-Liquid luck.
-Yes. Miss Granger. Liquid luck.

399
00:33:42,399 --> 00:33:45,277
Desperately tricky to make.
disastrous should you get it wrong.

400
00:33:46,039 --> 00:33:50,829
One sip and you will find
that all of your endeavors succeed.

401
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:55,189
At least until the effects wear off.

402
00:33:55,999 --> 00:33:59,674
So this is what I offer each of you today.

403
00:33:59,839 --> 00:34:04,469
One tiny vial of liquid luck to the student
who. in the hour that remains...

404
00:34:04,639 --> 00:34:09,030
...manages to brew an acceptable
Draught of Living Death...

405
00:34:09,199 --> 00:34:12,316
...the recipes for which can be found
on page 10 of your books.

406
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:15,995
I should point out. however. only once did
a student manage to brew a potion...

407
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:19,357
...of sufficient quality to claim this prize.

408
00:34:19,999 --> 00:34:22,069
Nevertheless. good luck to you all.

409
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,638
Let the brewing commence.

410
00:34:58,999 --> 00:35:00,751
How did you do that?

411
00:35:01,279 --> 00:35:03,349
You crush it. Don't cut it.

412
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:05,909
No. The instructions
specifically say to cut.

413
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:07,832
No. really.

414
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:46,837
Merlin's beard! It is perfect.

415
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:51,352
So perfect I daresay
one drop would kill us all.

416
00:35:54,519 --> 00:35:56,396
So here we are. then. as promised.

417
00:35:56,559 --> 00:35:59,631
One vial of Felix Felicis.

418
00:35:59,799 --> 00:36:01,755
Congratulations.

419
00:36:02,239 --> 00:36:04,878
Use it well.

420
00:36:24,479 --> 00:36:26,356
[KNOCKING]

421
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:33,920
DUMBLEDORE:
Harry. you got my message. Come in.

422
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:36,839
How are you?

423
00:36:36,999 --> 00:36:38,478
I'm fine. sir.

424
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:39,834
Enjoying your classes?

425
00:36:41,039 --> 00:36:43,951
I know Professor Slughorn
is most impressed with you.

426
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,835
I think he overestimates my abilities. sir.

427
00:36:47,520 --> 00:36:48,589
Do you?

428
00:36:49,119 --> 00:36:50,313
Definitely.

429
00:36:50,480 --> 00:36:52,072
[DUMBLEDORE CHUCKLES]

430
00:36:52,239 --> 00:36:54,958
What about your activities
outside the classroom?

431
00:36:56,119 --> 00:36:58,030
-Sir?
-Well. I notice you spend...

432
00:36:58,199 --> 00:37:00,713
...a great deal of time with Miss Granger.

433
00:37:00,879 --> 00:37:02,073
I can't help wondering....

434
00:37:02,239 --> 00:37:07,029
Oh. no. no. I mean. she's brilliant.
and we're friends. but. no.

435
00:37:07,199 --> 00:37:10,077
Forgive me. I was merely being curious.

436
00:37:11,119 --> 00:37:12,916
But enough chitchat.

437
00:37:13,119 --> 00:37:16,555
You must be wondering
why I summoned you here tonight.

438
00:37:17,119 --> 00:37:19,838
The answer lies here.

439
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:22,870
What you are looking at are memories.

440
00:37:23,039 --> 00:37:26,714
In this case.
pertaining to one individual. Voldemort...

441
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:29,235
...or. as he was known then. Tom Riddle.

442
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:35,835
This vial contains
the most particular memory...

443
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:38,116
...of the day I first met him.

444
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:42,073
I'd like you to see it. if you would.

445
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:22,233
WOMAN: I admit some confusion upon
receiving your letter, Mr. Dumbledore.

446
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:25,870
In all the years Tom's been here.
he's never once had a family visitor.

447
00:38:26,039 --> 00:38:29,634
There have been incidents
with the other children. Nasty things.

448
00:38:31,959 --> 00:38:34,029
Tom. you have a visitor.

449
00:38:34,560 --> 00:38:36,152
How do you do. Tom?

450
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,554
Don't.

451
00:38:52,039 --> 00:38:55,031
-You're the doctor. aren't you?
-No.

452
00:38:55,199 --> 00:38:57,155
I am a professor.

453
00:38:57,839 --> 00:38:59,591
I don't believe you.

454
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:01,671
She wants me looked at.

455
00:39:02,239 --> 00:39:04,355
They think I'm different.

456
00:39:04,519 --> 00:39:05,952
Well. perhaps they're right.

457
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:07,519
I'm not mad.

458
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:10,877
Hogwarts is not a place for mad people.

459
00:39:11,039 --> 00:39:12,950
Hogwarts is a school.

460
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:14,795
A school of magic.

461
00:39:19,119 --> 00:39:21,758
You can do things. can't you. Tom?

462
00:39:22,839 --> 00:39:25,399
Things other children can't.

463
00:39:26,719 --> 00:39:29,552
I can make things move
without touching them.

464
00:39:30,439 --> 00:39:33,875
I can make animals do what I want
without training them.

465
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:38,030
I can make bad things happen
to people who are mean to me.

466
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:40,517
I can make them hurt...

467
00:39:41,119 --> 00:39:42,598
...if I want.

468
00:39:43,119 --> 00:39:44,916
Who are you?

469
00:39:45,080 --> 00:39:47,196
Well. I'm like you. Tom.

470
00:39:48,319 --> 00:39:49,718
I'm different.

471
00:39:50,719 --> 00:39:52,072
Prove it.

472
00:39:59,359 --> 00:40:03,034
I think there's something in your wardrobe
trying to get out. Tom.

473
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:15,989
Thievery is not tolerated at Hogwarts.
Tom.

474
00:40:16,159 --> 00:40:21,597
At Hogwarts. you'll be taught not only
how to use magic. but how to control it.

475
00:40:21,759 --> 00:40:22,874
You understand me?

476
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:29,114
I can speak to snakes too.

477
00:40:30,319 --> 00:40:32,037
They find me.

478
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,831
Whisper things.

479
00:40:35,079 --> 00:40:38,071
Is that normal for someone like me?

480
00:40:58,280 --> 00:41:01,431
Did you know. sir? Then?

481
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:06,993
Did I know I'd just met the most
dangerous dark wizard of all time? No.

482
00:41:07,560 --> 00:41:09,596
If I had. I....

