00:59:08,239 --> 00:59:11,470
-You could be expelled for that.
-I don't know what you're talking about.

722
00:59:13,600 --> 00:59:16,114
Come on. Harry.
We've got a game to win.

723
00:59:37,360 --> 00:59:38,793
[CROWD CHEERING]

724
00:59:38,960 --> 00:59:40,791
Yes!

725
00:59:41,199 --> 00:59:43,918
MAN:
Go on. Ron! Do it!

726
01:00:14,400 --> 01:00:16,311
[CROWD CHEERING]

727
01:00:16,479 --> 01:00:18,674
CROWD [CHANTING]:
Weasley! Weasley! Weasley!

728
01:00:19,120 --> 01:00:20,439
Yes!

729
01:00:20,600 --> 01:00:23,910
Weasley! Weasley! Weasley!

730
01:00:27,559 --> 01:00:29,072
Whoo!

731
01:00:29,239 --> 01:00:32,311
Yes. Whoo!

732
01:00:33,799 --> 01:00:38,634
Weasley! Weasley! Weasley!

733
01:00:42,720 --> 01:00:44,358
You really shouldn't have done it.

734
01:00:44,519 --> 01:00:49,309
I know. I suppose I could've
just used a Confundus Charm.

735
01:00:50,279 --> 01:00:54,716
That was different. That was tryouts.
This was an actual game.

736
01:00:57,399 --> 01:00:59,037
You didn't put it in.

737
01:01:00,680 --> 01:01:02,432
Ron only thought you did.

738
01:01:05,079 --> 01:01:07,195
[CROWD CHEERING]

739
01:01:25,960 --> 01:01:28,633
[HERMlONE SNIFFLING]

740
01:01:30,279 --> 01:01:33,112
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

741
01:01:48,279 --> 01:01:51,430
Charms spell. I'm just practicing.

742
01:01:55,200 --> 01:01:56,952
Well. they're really good.

743
01:02:02,240 --> 01:02:04,151
How does it feel. Harry?

744
01:02:06,880 --> 01:02:09,952
When you see Dean with Ginny?

745
01:02:14,839 --> 01:02:16,238
I know.

746
01:02:17,279 --> 01:02:19,349
I see the way you look at her.

747
01:02:20,039 --> 01:02:21,597
You're my best friend.

748
01:02:23,920 --> 01:02:27,515
[LAVENDER LAUGHING]

749
01:02:30,320 --> 01:02:32,072
Oops.

750
01:02:33,439 --> 01:02:35,589
I think this room's taken.

751
01:02:37,280 --> 01:02:38,633
What's with the birds?

752
01:02:41,879 --> 01:02:43,517
Oppugnu.

753
01:03:10,400 --> 01:03:12,038
It feels like this.

754
01:03:50,119 --> 01:03:53,031
Look. I can't help it
if she's got her knickers in a twist.

755
01:03:53,199 --> 01:03:58,068
What Lav and I have. well.
let's just say. there's no stopping it.

756
01:03:58,240 --> 01:03:59,593
It's chemical.

757
01:03:59,760 --> 01:04:03,912
Will it last? Who knows?
Point is. I'm a free agent.

758
01:04:04,080 --> 01:04:06,799
HERMlONE: He's at perfect liberty
to kiss whoever he likes.

759
01:04:06,960 --> 01:04:09,269
I really couldn't careless.

760
01:04:09,440 --> 01:04:13,115
Was I under the impression he and I would
be attending Slughorn's Christmas party?

761
01:04:13,279 --> 01:04:14,712
Yes.

762
01:04:14,880 --> 01:04:19,112
Now. given the circumstances.
I've had to make other arrangements.

763
01:04:19,279 --> 01:04:20,428
Have you?

764
01:04:20,599 --> 01:04:22,510
Yes. Why?

765
01:04:22,679 --> 01:04:26,149
I just thought. seeing as neither of us
can go with who we'd really like to...

766
01:04:26,320 --> 01:04:28,470
...we should go together. as friends.

767
01:04:28,640 --> 01:04:30,198
Why didn't I think of that?

768
01:04:30,359 --> 01:04:31,838
Who are you going with?

769
01:04:32,000 --> 01:04:33,718
Um. it's a surprise.

770
01:04:33,879 --> 01:04:37,918
Anyway. it's you we've got to worry
about. You can't just take anyone.

771
01:04:38,519 --> 01:04:40,316
See that girl over there?

772
01:04:41,879 --> 01:04:46,395
That's Romilda Vane. Apparently she's
trying to smuggle you a love potion.

773
01:04:46,560 --> 01:04:47,993
ReaHy?

774
01:04:48,919 --> 01:04:52,229
Hey! She's only interested in you because
she thinks you're the Chosen One.

775
01:04:52,400 --> 01:04:54,038
But I am the Chosen One.

776
01:04:54,199 --> 01:04:56,952
Okay. sorry. Um. kidding.

777
01:04:58,879 --> 01:05:00,278
I'll ask someone I like.

778
01:05:01,040 --> 01:05:02,519
Someone cool.

779
01:05:11,879 --> 01:05:14,791
LUNA:
I've never been to this part of the castle.

780
01:05:14,960 --> 01:05:18,077
At least not while awake.
I sleepwalk. you see.

781
01:05:18,239 --> 01:05:20,628
That's why I wear shoes to bed.

782
01:05:50,560 --> 01:05:53,438
Harmonia Nectere Passus.

783
01:06:05,439 --> 01:06:08,078
Harmonia Nectere Passus.

784
01:06:09,559 --> 01:06:12,119
Harmonia Nectere Passus.

785
01:06:26,160 --> 01:06:27,513
Drink?

786
01:06:28,400 --> 01:06:29,674
Neville.

787
01:06:29,840 --> 01:06:31,239
I didn't get into the Slug Club.

788
01:06:31,399 --> 01:06:34,391
It's okay. though. He's got Belby
handing out towels in the loo.

789
01:06:34,560 --> 01:06:37,233
-Oh. well. I'm fine. mate. Thanks.
-Okay.

790
01:06:47,240 --> 01:06:50,073
Hermione. What are you doing?
And what happened to you?

791
01:06:50,240 --> 01:06:55,314
I've just escaped.
I mean. left Cormac under the mistletoe.

792
01:06:55,479 --> 01:06:58,391
Cormac? That's who you invited?

793
01:06:58,560 --> 01:07:00,949
I thought it would annoy Ron the most.

794
01:07:01,760 --> 01:07:03,671
SLUGHORN:
Thank you. I'll catch up with you later.

795
01:07:03,840 --> 01:07:06,718
He's got more tentacles
than a Snarfalump plant.

796
01:07:06,880 --> 01:07:08,950
-Dragon tartare?
-No. I'm fine. Thank you.

797
01:07:09,120 --> 01:07:11,680
Just as well.
They give one horribly bad breath.

798
01:07:11,840 --> 01:07:13,592
On second thoughts. . ..

799
01:07:13,760 --> 01:07:15,671
Might keep Cormac at bay.

800
01:07:15,999 --> 01:07:18,797
Oh. God. here he comes.

801
01:07:21,240 --> 01:07:23,993
I think she just went to powder her nose.

802
01:07:24,159 --> 01:07:26,150
CORMAC:
Slippery little minx. your friend.

803
01:07:26,319 --> 01:07:28,913
Likes to work her mouth too.
doesn't she?

804
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:33,751
What is this I'm eating. by the way?

805
01:07:34,880 --> 01:07:36,438
Dragon balls.

806
01:07:40,320 --> 01:07:42,356
[VOMITS]

807
01:07:47,199 --> 01:07:50,191
You've just bought yourself
a month's detention. McLaggen.

808
01:07:50,359 --> 01:07:54,068
Not so quick. Potter.

809
01:07:55,559 --> 01:07:58,551
Sir. I really think I should
rejoin the party. My date....

810
01:07:58,719 --> 01:08:02,473
Can surely survive your absence
for another minute or two.

811
01:08:02,640 --> 01:08:04,790
Besides. I only wish
to convey a message.

812
01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:07,550
-A message?
-From Professor Dumbledore.

813
01:08:07,719 --> 01:08:11,234
He asked me to give you his best.
and he hopes you enjoy your holiday.

814
01:08:11,400 --> 01:08:12,879
You see...

815
01:08:13,040 --> 01:08:18,353
...he's traveling. and he won't
return until term resumes.

816
01:08:18,520 --> 01:08:19,999
Traveling where?

817
01:08:27,799 --> 01:08:29,596
Take your hands off me. you filthy Squib!

818
01:08:30,679 --> 01:08:32,317
FILCH:
Professor Slughorn. sir.

819
01:08:32,480 --> 01:08:36,632
I just discovered this boy
lurking in an upstairs corridor.

820
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:38,756
He claims to have been
invited to your party.

821
01:08:38,920 --> 01:08:42,071
Okay. okay. I was gatecrashing. Happy?

822
01:08:42,240 --> 01:08:45,915
I'll escort him out.

823
01:08:48,600 --> 01:08:52,115
Certainly. professor.

824
01:08:55,599 --> 01:08:58,716
All right. everyone. carry on. carry on.

825
01:09:00,720 --> 01:09:05,430
DRACO: Maybe I did hex that Bell girl.
Maybe I didn't. What's it to you?

826
01:09:05,600 --> 01:09:07,591
SNAPE:
I swore to protect you.

827
01:09:07,760 --> 01:09:10,957
I made the Unbreakable Vow.

828
01:09:11,119 --> 01:09:13,189
DRACO:
I don't need protection.

829
01:09:13,359 --> 01:09:17,352
I was chosen for this.
Out of all others. Me.

830
01:09:18,240 --> 01:09:21,630
-And I won't fail him.
-You're afraid. Draco.

831
01:09:22,199 --> 01:09:25,953
You attempt to conceal it.
but it's obvious. Let me assist you.

832
01:09:26,120 --> 01:09:27,519
DRACO:
No!

833
01:09:27,839 --> 01:09:31,115
I was chosen. This is my moment.

834
01:09:43,040 --> 01:09:44,553
RON:
“Unbreakable Vow.“

835
01:09:44,720 --> 01:09:46,278
You're sure that's what Snape said?

836
01:09:46,439 --> 01:09:48,634
Positive. Why?

837
01:09:48,800 --> 01:09:52,156
Well. it's just you can't break
an Unbreakable Vow.

838
01:09:52,319 --> 01:09:55,516
I'd worked that much out for myself.
funnily enough.

839
01:09:56,000 --> 01:09:57,672
You don't understand.

840
01:09:58,279 --> 01:09:59,268
Oh. bloody hell.

841
01:10:25,960 --> 01:10:27,837
I miss you.

842
01:10:29,480 --> 01:10:30,959
Lovely.

843
01:10:31,119 --> 01:10:34,270
All she wants to do is snog me.
My lips are getting chapped. Look.

844
01:10:34,439 --> 01:10:36,555
I'll take your word for it.

845
01:10:46,240 --> 01:10:50,995
So. what happens to you? What happens
if you break an Unbreakable Vow?

846
01:10:51,520 --> 01:10:53,158
You die.

847
01:10:57,560 --> 01:10:59,357
WOMAN:
Wait. the pudding's still here.

848
01:11:00,560 --> 01:11:03,757
REMUS: Voldemort has chosen
Draco Malfoy for a mission?

849
01:11:03,920 --> 01:11:04,955
I know it sounds mad.

850
01:11:05,120 --> 01:11:08,476
Has it occurred to you Snape was
simply pretending to offer Draco help...

851
01:11:08,640 --> 01:11:11,029
...so he could find out
what he was up to?

852
01:11:11,200 --> 01:11:14,078
-That's not what it sounded like.
NYMPHADORA: Perhaps Harry's right.

853
01:11:14,600 --> 01:11:16,158
To make an Unbreakable Vow. it's--

854
01:11:16,319 --> 01:11:19,675
It comes down to whether or not
you trust Dumbledore's judgment.

855
01:11:19,839 --> 01:11:23,752
-Dumb|edore trusts Snape. therefore I do.
-Dumb|edore can make mistakes.

856
01:11:23,920 --> 01:11:25,035
You're blinded by hatred.

857
01:11:25,200 --> 01:11:27,156
-|'m not.
-Yes. you are.

858
01:11:28,839 --> 01:11:31,717
People are disappearing. Harry. daily.

859
01:11:31,879 --> 01:11:33,756
We place our trust
in a handful of people.

860
01:11:33,920 --> 01:11:36,753
If we start fighting amongst ourselves.
we're doomed.

861
01:12:00,240 --> 01:12:01,719
Open up. you.

862
01:12:03,319 --> 01:12:04,877
Don't you trust me?

863
01:12:10,879 --> 01:12:11,914
It's good.

864
01:12:12,800 --> 01:12:15,519
RON:
Yeah. I'll just-- Get-- Yeah.

865
01:12:22,000 --> 01:12:24,673
-Pie?
-Not for me. no.

866
01:12:36,119 --> 01:12:37,598
ARTHUR:
You'll have to forgive Remus.

867
01:12:37,839 --> 01:12:40,558
It takes its toll. his condition.

868
01:12:41,439 --> 01:12:43,395
HARRY:
Are you all right. Mr. Weasley?

869
01:12:43,560 --> 01:12:45,994
We're being followed. all of us.

870
01:12:46,160 --> 01:12:48,549
Most days.
Molly doesn't leave the house.

871
01:12:49,360 --> 01:12:51,351
It's not been easy.

872
01:12:53,279 --> 01:12:54,632
Did you get my owl?

873
01:12:54,800 --> 01:12:56,791
Yes. I did.

874
01:12:58,239 --> 01:13:01,151
If Dumbledore's traveling.
then that's news to the Ministry...

875
01:13:01,319 --> 01:13:03,674
...but perhaps that's the way
Dumbledore wants it.

876
01:13:04,360 --> 01:13:06,749
As for Draco Malfoy...

877
01:13:07,360 --> 01:13:08,475
...I know a bit more.

878
01:13:09,080 --> 01:13:11,992
-Go on.
-I sent an agent to Borgin and Burkes.

879
01:13:12,160 --> 01:13:14,390
I think. from what you described...

880
01:13:14,560 --> 01:13:16,152
...what you and Ron saw in summer...

881
01:13:16,319 --> 01:13:19,675
...the object
that Draco is so interested in...

882
01:13:19,840 --> 01:13:21,273
...is a vanishing cabinet.

883
01:13:22,119 --> 01:13:23,347
A vanishing cabinet?

884
01:13:23,519 --> 01:13:27,353
They were all the rage
when Voldemort first rose to power.

885
01:13:27,519 --> 01:13:30,352
You can see the appeal.
Should Death Eaters come knocking...

886
01:13:30,519 --> 01:13:35,070
...one simply had to slip inside
and disappear for an hour or two.

887
01:13:35,679 --> 01:13:37,351
They can transport you anywhere.

888
01:13:37,519 --> 01:13:40,750
Tricky contraptions though.
very temperamental.

889
01:13:40,919 --> 01:13:43,717
What happened to it?
The one at Borgin and Burkes?

890
01:13:43,879 --> 01:13:44,948
Nothing.

891
01:13:45,760 --> 01:13:47,398
It's still there.

892
01:13:58,040 --> 01:13:59,678
NYMPHADORA:
It was delicious. Molly. really.

893
01:13:59,840 --> 01:14:01,114
MOLLY:
Are you sure you won't stay?

894
01:14:01,279 --> 01:14:05,477
No. we should go. The first night
of the cycle's always the worst.

895
01:14:05,640 --> 01:14:06,629
Remus?

896
01:14:15,199 --> 01:14:16,678
Sweetheart.

897
01:14:24,639 --> 01:14:26,311
Has Ron gone to bed?

898
01:14:26,479 --> 01:14:29,198
Um.... Not yet. No.

899
01:14:30,920 --> 01:14:32,194
Shoelace.

900
01:14:44,280 --> 01:14:46,077
Merry Christmas. Harry.

901
01:14:47,440 --> 01:14:48,919
Merry Christmas.

902
01:15:05,480 --> 01:15:07,675
-Harry. no!
-Remus!

903
01:15:17,120 --> 01:15:18,473
Ginny!

904
01:15:21,519 --> 01:15:25,990
BELLATRIX: I killed Sirius Black!
I killed Sirius Black!

905
01:15:26,160 --> 01:15:28,310
You coming to get me?

906
01:15:29,359 --> 01:15:32,556
Harry. can you get me?
You coming to get me?

907
01:16:01,080 --> 01:16:02,399
Harry?

908
01:16:19,200 --> 01:16:20,792
Stupely!

909
01:16:42,719 --> 01:16:44,391
ARTHUR:
Harry!

910
01:16:57,359 --> 01:16:58,508
Ginny!

911
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:28,313
Molly.

912
01:17:50,359 --> 01:17:51,997
HERMlONE:
It's easy for them to get to you.

913
01:17:52,159 --> 01:17:56,118
You're bloody lucky you weren't killed.
You have to realize who you are. Harry.

914
01:17:56,279 --> 01:17:58,713
I know who I am. Hermione. all right?

915
01:17:59,639 --> 01:18:00,788
Sorry.

916
01:18:02,399 --> 01:18:05,596
Lav. come on. Of course I'll wear it.

917
01:18:05,759 --> 01:18:07,829
That's my Won-Won.

918
01:18:09,759 --> 01:18:12,068
Excuse me. I have to go and vomit.

919
01:18:29,000 --> 01:18:31,195
SLUGHORN: I'd like to know
where you get your information.

920
01:18:31,360 --> 01:18:34,272
More knowledgeable
than half the staff, you are.

921
01:18:39,679 --> 01:18:41,158
Sir...

922
01:18:41,599 --> 01:18:44,318
...is it true
that Professor Merrythought is retiring?

923
01:18:44,479 --> 01:18:47,152
Now. Tom.
I couldn't tell you if I knew. could I?

924
01:18:47,400 --> 01:18:51,393
By the way. thank you for the pineapple.
You're quite right. it is my favorite.

925
01:18:51,960 --> 01:18:54,155
But how did you know?

926
01:18:55,920 --> 01:18:57,433
Intuition.

927
01:18:59,919 --> 01:19:01,272
[CLOCK CHIMING]

928
01:19:01,439 --> 01:19:03,077
SLUGHORN:
Gracious. Is it that time already?

929
01:19:03,239 --> 01:19:06,754
Off you go. boys. or Professor Dippet
will have us all in detention.

930
01:19:10,720 --> 01:19:14,395
Look sharp. Tom. Don't want to be caught
out of bed after hours.

931
01:19:16,240 --> 01:19:18,231
-Is something on your mind. Tom?
-Yes. sir.

932
01:19:19,520 --> 01:19:22,239
You see. I couldn't think
of anyone else to go to.

933
01:19:23,120 --> 01:19:27,910
The other professors.
well. they're not like you.

934
01:19:28,280 --> 01:19:31,192
They might misunderstand.

935
01:19:31,360 --> 01:19:32,873
Go on.

936
01:19:33,639 --> 01:19:35,834
I was in the library the other night...

937
01:19:36,359 --> 01:19:38,475
...in the Restricted Section...

938
01:19:39,199 --> 01:19:42,589
...and I read something rather odd
about a bit of rare magic.

939
01:19:43,479 --> 01:19:46,835
And I thought perhaps
you could illuminate me.

940
01:19:47,000 --> 01:19:49,673
It's called. as I understand it....

941
01:19:50,879 --> 01:19:52,312
[RIDDLE SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

942
01:19:52,480 --> 01:19:53,595
I beg your pardon?

943
01:19:53,759 --> 01:19:57,195
I don't know anything about such things.
and if I did. I wouldn't tell you!

944
01:19:57,359 --> 01:20:01,955
Now. get out of here at once. and don't
let me ever catch you mentioning it again!

945
01:20:04,800 --> 01:20:05,915
DUMBLEDORE:
Confused?

946
01:20:06,559 --> 01:20:07,992
I'd be surprised if you weren't.

947
01:20:08,879 --> 01:20:11,518
Well. I don't understand.
What happened?

948
01:20:11,680 --> 01:20:15,195
This is perhaps the most important
memory I've collected.

949
01:20:15,519 --> 01:20:17,191
It is also a lie.

950
01:20:18,079 --> 01:20:19,797
This memory has been tampered with...

951
01:20:19,960 --> 01:20:24,158
...by the same person whose memory it is.
our old friend. Professor Slughorn.

952
01:20:24,759 --> 01:20:26,670
But why would he tamper
with his own memory?

953
01:20:26,840 --> 01:20:29,593
-I suspect he's ashamed of it.
-Why?

954
01:20:29,759 --> 01:20:31,192
Why. indeed?

955
01:20:31,960 --> 01:20:35,191
I asked you to get to know
Professor Slughorn. and you have done so.

956
01:20:35,359 --> 01:20:38,829
Now I want you to persuade him
to divulge his true memory...

957
01:20:39,000 --> 01:20:40,479
...any way you can.

958
01:20:40,640 --> 01:20:42,517
I don't know him that well. sir.

959
01:20:46,800 --> 01:20:49,598
This memory is everything.

960
01:20:50,080 --> 01:20:51,991
Without it. we are blind.

961
01:20:52,479 --> 01:20:55,949
Without it. we leave the fate
of our world to chance.

962
01:20:57,920 --> 01:20:59,672
You have no choice.

963
01:21:00,840 --> 01:21:02,751
You must not fail.

964
01:21:10,520 --> 01:21:12,750
SLUGHORN: So I'd highly recommend
you reacquaint yourself...

965
01:21:12,920 --> 01:21:14,319
...with the chapter on antidotes.

966
01:21:14,479 --> 01:21:18,074
I'll tell you more about bezoars
in our next class. Right. off you go.

967
01:21:18,239 --> 01:21:20,628
Alys. don't forget your rat tail.

968
01:21:25,879 --> 01:21:29,508
Aha. If it isn't
the Prince of Potions himself.

969
01:21:29,680 --> 01:21:31,511
To what do I owe this pleasure?

970
01:21:32,639 --> 01:21:34,630
Sir. I wondered
if I might ask you something.

971
01:21:34,800 --> 01:21:36,950
Ask away. dear boy. ask away.

972
01:21:37,120 --> 01:21:39,998
The other day I was in the library.
in the Restricted Section...

973
01:21:40,159 --> 01:21:43,674
...and I came across something rather odd
about a very rare piece of magic.

974
01:21:44,959 --> 01:21:47,519
Yes. And what was this
rare piece of magic?

975
01:21:47,680 --> 01:21:50,877
Well. I don't know.
I can't remember the name exactly.

976
01:21:51,039 --> 01:21:55,191
It got me wondering. are there some kinds
of magic you're not allowed to teach us?

977
01:21:57,120 --> 01:21:58,394
SLUGHORN:
I'm Potions Master. Harry.

978
01:21:58,560 --> 01:22:01,279
I think your question'd
better be posed to Professor Snape.

979
01:22:01,439 --> 01:22:03,270
HARRY:
Yes. Um....

980
01:22:03,439 --> 01:22:05,828
He and I don't exactly
see eye to eye. sir.

981
01:22:06,000 --> 01:22:07,718
What I mean to say is...

982
01:22:08,520 --> 01:22:10,238
...well. he's not like you.

983
01:22:10,879 --> 01:22:12,631
He might misunderstand.

984
01:22:13,879 --> 01:22:17,554
Yes. There can be no light
without the dark.

985
01:22:17,720 --> 01:22:21,599
And so it is with magic. Myself. I always
strive to live within the light.

986
01:22:22,200 --> 01:22:23,792
I suggest you do the same.

987
01:22:24,159 --> 01:22:27,037
Is that what you told Tom Riddle.
when he came asking questions?

988
01:22:33,720 --> 01:22:36,632
Dumbledore put you up to this.
didn't he?

989
01:22:38,560 --> 01:22:40,118
Didn't he?

990
01:22:45,280 --> 01:22:47,032
[KNOCKING]

991
01:22:47,200 --> 01:22:48,428
Yes?

992
01:22:48,800 --> 01:22:50,836
Oh. it's you. Potter.

993
01:22:51,000 --> 01:22:53,275
I'm sorry. I'm busy at the moment.

994
01:23:05,559 --> 01:23:09,188
It's beautiful. isn't it? The moon.

995
01:23:10,159 --> 01:23:11,512
HARRY:
Divine.

996
01:23:12,159 --> 01:23:14,354
Had ourselves a little
late-night snack. did we?

997
01:23:15,440 --> 01:23:18,876
It was on your bed. the box.
I just thought I'd try one.

998
01:23:19,039 --> 01:23:22,395
HARRY: Or 20.
-I can't stop thinking about her. Harry.

999
01:23:22,559 --> 01:23:24,470
Honestly. I reckoned
she was annoying you.

1000
01:23:24,640 --> 01:23:26,870
She could never annoy me.

1001
01:23:28,600 --> 01:23:30,079
I think I love her.

1002
01:23:33,519 --> 01:23:35,714
Well. brilliant.

1003
01:23:39,400 --> 01:23:40,958
Do you think she knows I exist?

1004
01:23:41,120 --> 01:23:43,509
I hope so. She's been snogging you
for three months.

1005
01:23:43,680 --> 01:23:46,513
Snogging? Who are you talking about?

1006
01:23:47,399 --> 01:23:48,593
Who are you talking about?

1007
01:23:49,320 --> 01:23:52,790
Romilda. of course. Romilda Vane.

1008
01:23:52,959 --> 01:23:54,392
Okay. very funny.

1009
01:23:57,399 --> 01:24:00,914
-What was that for?
-|t's no joke! I'm in love with her!

1010
01:24:01,079 --> 01:24:03,832
Fine. you're in love with her.
Have you ever actually met her?

1011
01:24:04,760 --> 01:24:07,593
No. Can you introduce me?

1012
01:24:28,399 --> 01:24:32,950
Come on. Ron. I'm gonna introduce you
to Romilda Vane.

1013
01:24:41,120 --> 01:24:43,111
[KNOCKING]

1014
01:24:43,279 --> 01:24:46,828
I'm sorry. sir. I wouldn't bother you
if it weren't absolutely essential.

1015
01:24:47,640 --> 01:24:48,993
RON:
Where's Romilda?

1016
01:24:49,159 --> 01:24:51,036
What's the matter with Wenby?

1017
01:24:51,519 --> 01:24:53,271
HARRY [WHISPERS]:
Very powerful love potion.

1018
01:24:53,439 --> 01:24:55,714
SLUGHORN:
Very well. Better bring him in.

1019
01:24:55,880 --> 01:24:59,031
I'd have thought you could whip up
a remedy for this in no time. Harry.

1020
01:24:59,199 --> 01:25:01,997
Well. I thought this called
for a more practiced hand. sir.

1021
01:25:02,159 --> 01:25:05,117
Hello. darling. Fancy a drink?

1022
01:25:05,279 --> 01:25:06,871
Perhaps you're right.

1023
01:25:11,199 --> 01:25:16,398
HARRY: I'm sorry. by the way. professor.
about earlier today. our misunderstanding.

1024
01:25:16,559 --> 01:25:20,757
Oh. not at all. All water
under the bridge. you know? Correct?

1025
01:25:20,919 --> 01:25:23,717
I expect you're tired of it
after all these years.

1026
01:25:23,880 --> 01:25:26,348
All the questions about Voldemort.

1027
01:25:26,519 --> 01:25:28,271
Don't use that name.

1028
01:25:31,039 --> 01:25:32,677
[THUDS]

1029
01:25:35,679 --> 01:25:37,670
SLUGHORN:
There you are. old boy. Bottoms up.

1030
01:25:37,839 --> 01:25:40,831
-What's this?
SLUGHORN: Tonic for the nerves.

1031
01:25:54,760 --> 01:25:56,955
-What happened to me?
-Love potion.

1032
01:25:57,120 --> 01:25:59,156
A bloody strong one at that.

1033
01:25:59,719 --> 01:26:03,189
-| feel really bad.
SLUGHORN: You need a pick-me-up.

1034
01:26:03,359 --> 01:26:06,874
Got Butterbeer.
wine. dazzling oak-matured mead.

1035
01:26:07,039 --> 01:26:11,191
I had other intentions for this.
but I think. given the circumstances....

1036
01:26:13,399 --> 01:26:15,037
Here we are. Potter.

1037
01:26:15,200 --> 01:26:16,633
To life!

1038
01:26:21,240 --> 01:26:22,229
HARRY:
Ron.

1039
01:26:24,600 --> 01:26:27,910
Ron. Professor. do something.

1040
01:26:28,959 --> 01:26:30,517
SLUGHORN:
I don't understand.

1041
01:26:46,239 --> 01:26:47,957
HARRY:
Come on. Ron. breathe.

1042
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:02,318
[COUGHING]

1043
01:27:09,279 --> 01:27:11,998
These girls. they're gonna kill me.

1044
01:27:22,560 --> 01:27:25,791
Ouick thinking on your part. Harry.
using a bezoar.

1045
01:27:25,959 --> 01:27:28,234
You must be very proud
of your student. Horace.

1046
01:27:28,399 --> 01:27:31,675
Hm? Oh. yes. very proud.

1047
01:27:31,839 --> 01:27:34,478
I think we agree.
Potter's actions were heroic.

1048
01:27:34,640 --> 01:27:38,474
The question is.
why were they necessary?

1049
01:27:38,640 --> 01:27:40,312
DUMBLEDORE:
Why. indeed?

1050
01:27:40,479 --> 01:27:42,390
This appears to be a gift. Horace.

1051
01:27:42,720 --> 01:27:45,439
You don't remember
who gave you this bottle?

1052
01:27:45,600 --> 01:27:49,388
Which. by the way. possesses remarkably
subtle hints of licorice and cherry...

1053
01:27:49,560 --> 01:27:51,915
...when not polluted with poison.

1054
01:27:52,079 --> 01:27:55,071
SLUGHORN: Actually I had intended
to give it as a gift myself.

1055
01:27:55,239 --> 01:27:56,558
To whom. I might ask?

1056
01:27:58,320 --> 01:28:00,390
To you. Headmaster.

1057
01:28:02,640 --> 01:28:03,675
LAVENDER:
Where is he?

1058
01:28:03,840 --> 01:28:07,799
Where's my Won-Won?
Has he been asking for me?

1059
01:28:10,719 --> 01:28:12,311
What's she doing here?

1060
01:28:12,480 --> 01:28:14,630
I might ask you the same question.

1061
01:28:14,800 --> 01:28:16,950
I happen to be his girlfriend.

1062
01:28:17,120 --> 01:28:19,759
I happen to be his friend.

1063
01:28:19,920 --> 01:28:23,959
Don't make me laugh.
You haven't spoken in weeks.

1064
01:28:24,720 --> 01:28:27,473
I suppose you want to make up
now that he's all interesting.

1065
01:28:27,640 --> 01:28:31,189
He's been poisoned. you daft dimbo!

1066
01:28:31,359 --> 01:28:34,078
And for the record.
I've always found him interesting.

1067
01:28:35,679 --> 01:28:40,514
Ah. See? He senses my presence.

1068
01:28:40,680 --> 01:28:43,831
Don't worry. Won-Won. I'm here.

1069
01:28:44,479 --> 01:28:46,231
I'm here.

1070
01:28:47,919 --> 01:28:49,716
[MUMBLES]

1071
01:28:51,840 --> 01:28:54,912
RON:
Uh.... Hermione....

1072
01:28:58,800 --> 01:29:00,711
Hermione.

1073
01:29:01,440 --> 01:29:03,590
Hermione.

1074
01:29:07,519 --> 01:29:09,794
[LAVENDER SOBBING]

1075
01:29:10,880 --> 01:29:14,634
Oh. to be young.
and to feel Iove's keen sting.

1076
01:29:14,959 --> 01:29:17,189
Well. come away. everybody.

1077
01:29:17,359 --> 01:29:19,873
Mr. Weasley is well tended.

1078
01:29:23,959 --> 01:29:26,393
About time. don't you think?

1079
01:29:28,959 --> 01:29:30,472
Thank you.

1080
01:29:33,279 --> 01:29:35,031
Oh. shut up.

1081
01:31:41,920 --> 01:31:45,549
Stop it. Ron. You're making it snow.

1082
01:31:49,839 --> 01:31:52,399
Tell me how I broke up
with Lavender again.

1083
01:31:53,199 --> 01:31:55,918
HERMlONE:
Um. well...

1084
01:31:56,080 --> 01:31:58,958
...she came to visit you
in the hospital.

1085
01:31:59,799 --> 01:32:02,108
And you talked.

1086
01:32:03,639 --> 01:32:07,552
I don't believe it was
a particularly long conversation.

1087
01:32:07,719 --> 01:32:10,870
Don't get me wrong. I'm bloody thrilled
to be shot of her.

1088
01:32:11,040 --> 01:32:13,270
It's just she seems a bit put out.

1089
01:32:19,520 --> 01:32:22,876
Yes. she does. doesn't she?

1090
01:32:24,439 --> 01:32:29,274
You say you don't remember
anything from that night?

1091
01:32:29,439 --> 01:32:32,317
Anything at all?

1092
01:32:32,480 --> 01:32:34,232
There is something.

1093
01:32:37,599 --> 01:32:41,877
But it can't be.
I was completely boggled. wasn't I?

1094
01:32:43,319 --> 01:32:46,391
Right. Boggled.

1095
01:32:53,360 --> 01:32:54,554
HERMlONE:
Harry.

1096
01:32:55,959 --> 01:32:57,074
That's Katie.

1097
01:32:58,959 --> 01:33:00,517
Katie Bell.

1098
01:33:07,880 --> 01:33:10,155
Katie. How are you?

1099
01:33:10,799 --> 01:33:15,111
I know you're going to ask. Harry.
but I don't know who cursed me.

1100
01:33:16,679 --> 01:33:20,069
I've been trying to remember. honestly.

1101
01:33:20,480 --> 01:33:23,756
But I just can't.

1102
01:33:36,479 --> 01:33:37,753
Katie?

1103
01:34:09,080 --> 01:34:11,230
[SOBBING]

1104
01:34:18,479 --> 01:34:22,392
HARRY: I know what you did. Malfoy.
You hexed her. didn't you?

1105
01:34:25,280 --> 01:34:28,317
[GRUNTING]

1106
01:34:51,519 --> 01:34:53,430
Sectumsempra!

1107
01:35:38,480 --> 01:35:41,278
SNAPE:
Vulnera Sanen tur.

1108
01:35:42,880 --> 01:35:45,599
Vulnera Sanen tur.

1109
01:35:47,799 --> 01:35:50,552
Vulnera Sanen tur.

1110
01:36:10,799 --> 01:36:14,189
You have to get rid of it. Today.

1111
01:36:18,880 --> 01:36:20,438
Take my hand.

1112
01:36:35,760 --> 01:36:37,591
The Room of Requirement.

1113
01:36:43,799 --> 01:36:46,313
GINNY: We need to hide
the Half-Blood Prince's book...

1114
01:36:46,479 --> 01:36:50,028
...where no one will ever find it.
including you.

1115
01:36:54,920 --> 01:36:56,876
[RUSTLING]

1116
01:36:58,040 --> 01:36:59,439
-What was that?
-What was that?

1117
01:37:07,640 --> 01:37:10,438
[RUSTLING CONTINUES]

1118
01:37:24,480 --> 01:37:25,754
See?

1119
01:37:26,280 --> 01:37:28,236
You never know what you'll find up here.

1120
01:37:46,599 --> 01:37:50,353
All right. close your eyes.
That way you can't be tempted.

1121
01:37:54,040 --> 01:37:55,678
Close your eyes.

1122
01:38:21,280 --> 01:38:24,033
That can stay hidden up here too.
if you like.

1123
01:38:38,079 --> 01:38:40,354
So did you and Ginny do it. then?

1124
01:38:40,519 --> 01:38:41,634
What?

1125
01:38:41,799 --> 01:38:43,790
You know. hide the book?

1126
01:38:43,959 --> 01:38:45,756
Oh. yeah.

1127
01:38:48,559 --> 01:38:51,027
Ah. Dear. yes.

1128
01:38:51,199 --> 01:38:53,872
Still no luck with Slughorn. then.
I take it?

1129
01:38:55,839 --> 01:38:57,113
Luck.

1130
01:38:58,119 --> 01:39:01,316
That's it. All I need's a bit of luck.

1131
01:39:18,720 --> 01:39:21,792
HERMlONE:
Well. how do you feel?

1132
01:39:21,960 --> 01:39:23,518
Excellent.

1133
01:39:24,640 --> 01:39:26,551
Really excellent.

1134
01:39:29,199 --> 01:39:30,712
Remember...

1135
01:39:31,040 --> 01:39:32,712
...Slughorn usually eats early...

1136
01:39:32,880 --> 01:39:35,758
...takes a walk.
and then returns to his office.

1137
01:39:35,920 --> 01:39:37,353
Right.

1138
01:39:37,759 --> 01:39:39,829
-|'m going down to Hagrid's.
-What?

1139
01:39:40,000 --> 01:39:42,560
No. Harry. you've got to go
and speak to Slughorn.

1140
01:39:44,079 --> 01:39:46,547
-We have a plan.
HARRY: I know...

1141
01:39:46,719 --> 01:39:48,710
...but I've got a
good feeling about Hagrid's.

1142
01:39:48,880 --> 01:39:52,475
I feel it's the place to be tonight.
Do you know what I mean?

1143
01:39:53,319 --> 01:39:55,469
-No.
-We||. trust me. I know what I'm doing.

1144
01:39:55,640 --> 01:39:57,710
Or Felix does.

1145
01:39:58,799 --> 01:40:00,232
Hi!

1146
01:40:27,880 --> 01:40:29,438
[GRUNTS]

1147
01:40:29,599 --> 01:40:31,237
Merlin's beard. Harry!

1148
01:40:31,399 --> 01:40:35,358
Sorry. sir. I should've announced myself.
Cleared my throat. coughed.

1149
01:40:35,520 --> 01:40:37,397
You probably feared
I was Professor Sprout.

1150
01:40:37,559 --> 01:40:40,835
Yes. I did. actually.
What makes you think that?

1151
01:40:40,999 --> 01:40:42,990
Well. just the general behavior. sir.

1152
01:40:43,159 --> 01:40:45,832
The sneaking around.
the jumping when you saw me.

1153
01:40:46,000 --> 01:40:49,436
Are those Tentacula leaves. sir?
They're very valuable. aren't they?

1154
01:40:49,599 --> 01:40:51,829
Ten Galleons a leaf to the right buyer.

1155
01:40:52,000 --> 01:40:55,356
Not that I'm familiar with any such
transactions. but one does hear rumors.

1156
01:40:55,519 --> 01:40:59,148
My own interests
are purely academic. of course.

1157
01:40:59,319 --> 01:41:02,470
Personally. these plants
always kind of freaked me out.

1158
01:41:05,599 --> 01:41:07,669
SLUGHORN:
How did you get out of the castle. Harry?

1159
01:41:07,839 --> 01:41:09,272
HARRY:
Through the front door. sir.

1160
01:41:09,439 --> 01:41:11,509
I'm off to Hagrid's.
He's a very dear friend...

1161
01:41:11,679 --> 01:41:13,317
...and I fancied paying him a visit.

1162
01:41:13,479 --> 01:41:15,674
So if you don't mind.
I will be going now.

1163
01:41:16,439 --> 01:41:17,997
Harry!

1164
01:41:18,799 --> 01:41:21,154
-Sir?
-|t's nearly nightfall.

1165
01:41:21,319 --> 01:41:24,629
Surely you realize I can't allow you
to go roaming the grounds by yourself.

1166
01:41:24,799 --> 01:41:27,267
Well. then. by all means. come along. sir.

1167
01:41:32,400 --> 01:41:35,472
SLUGHORN: Harry. I must insist
you accompany me...

1168
01:41:35,640 --> 01:41:37,312
...back to the castle immediately!

1169
01:41:37,479 --> 01:41:40,596
HARRY:
That would be counterproductive. sir.

1170
01:41:41,880 --> 01:41:43,916
And what makes you say that?

1171
01:41:44,959 --> 01:41:46,472
No idea.

1172
01:41:52,959 --> 01:41:54,312
Horace.

1173
01:41:54,920 --> 01:41:59,994
Merlin's beard.
Is that an actual Acromantula?

1174
01:42:00,559 --> 01:42:02,550
A dead one. I think. sir.

1175
01:42:03,319 --> 01:42:04,798
Good God.

1176
01:42:05,400 --> 01:42:08,358
Dear fellow.
however did you manage to kill it?

1177
01:42:08,640 --> 01:42:11,950
Kill it? Me oldest friend. he was.

1178
01:42:12,120 --> 01:42:16,159
-|'m so sorry. I didn't--
-Don't worry yourself. you're not alone.

1179
01:42:16,640 --> 01:42:19,950
Seriously misunderstood creatures.
spiders are.

1180
01:42:20,119 --> 01:42:22,235
It's the eyes. I reckon.
They unnerve some folk.

1181
01:42:22,640 --> 01:42:24,517
Not to mention the pincers.

1182
01:42:24,679 --> 01:42:26,556
[CLICKING TONGUE]

1183
01:42:28,640 --> 01:42:30,517
Yeah. I reckon that too.

1184
01:42:31,199 --> 01:42:34,430
Hagrid. the last thing
I wish to be is indelicate...

1185
01:42:34,599 --> 01:42:38,512
...but Acromantular venom
is uncommonly rare.

1186
01:42:38,679 --> 01:42:40,795
Would you allow me
to extract a vial or two?

1187
01:42:40,959 --> 01:42:43,473
Purely for academic purposes.
you understand.

1188
01:42:43,640 --> 01:42:46,438
Well. I don't suppose it's going
to do him much good now. is it?

1189
01:42:46,599 --> 01:42:47,748
My thoughts exactly.

1190
01:42:47,920 --> 01:42:54,155
Always have a ampoule or two about
my person for just such occasions as this.

1191
01:42:54,400 --> 01:42:59,190
Old Potions Master's habit. you know.

1192
01:42:59,840 --> 01:43:02,195
I wish you could've seen him
in his prime.

1193
01:43:02,359 --> 01:43:05,874
Magnificent. he was. Just magnificent.

1194
01:43:07,239 --> 01:43:08,752
Oh. dear.

1195
01:43:18,079 --> 01:43:21,151
-Would you like me to say a few words?
-Yes.

1196
01:43:21,400 --> 01:43:22,879
He had a family. I trust?

1197
01:43:23,040 --> 01:43:24,473
Oh. yeah.

1198
01:43:29,599 --> 01:43:31,032
Farewell....

1199
01:43:31,199 --> 01:43:32,996
Aragog.

1200
01:43:37,319 --> 01:43:40,117
Farewell. Aragog...

1201
01:43:40,479 --> 01:43:43,039
...king of the arachnids.

1202
01:43:43,839 --> 01:43:46,307
Your body will decay...

1203
01:43:47,520 --> 01:43:50,239
...but your spirit lingers on.

1204
01:43:50,920 --> 01:43:57,268
And your human friends find solace
in the loss they have sustained.

1205
01:43:57,640 --> 01:44:00,677
[SLUGHORN 8: HAGRID SINGING]

1206
01:44:11,839 --> 01:44:15,309
I had him from an egg. you know.
Tiny little thing he was when he hatched.

1207
01:44:15,479 --> 01:44:19,028
No bigger than a Pekinese.
A Pekinese. mind you.

1208
01:44:19,199 --> 01:44:24,148
How sweet. I once had a fish. Francis.
He was very dear to me.

1209
01:44:24,319 --> 01:44:29,268
One afternoon I came downstairs.
and he'd vanished.

1210
01:44:29,439 --> 01:44:30,952
Poof.

1211
01:44:31,120 --> 01:44:34,192
-That's very odd. isn't it?
-It is. isn't it?

1212
01:44:34,360 --> 01:44:37,909
But that's life. I suppose.

1213
01:44:38,080 --> 01:44:43,200
You go along and then suddenly. poof!

1214
01:44:43,360 --> 01:44:46,875
-Poof.
-Poof.

1215
01:44:51,359 --> 01:44:53,315
[HAGRID SNORING]

1216
01:45:00,839 --> 01:45:03,831
It was a student who gave me Francis.

1217
01:45:04,799 --> 01:45:08,917
One spring afternoon
I discovered a bowl on my desk...

1218
01:45:09,799 --> 01:45:12,632
...with just a few inches
of clear water in it.

1219
01:45:13,400 --> 01:45:16,790
And floating on the surface
was a flower petal.

1220
01:45:18,280 --> 01:45:20,635
As I watched. it sank.

1221
01:45:22,080 --> 01:45:24,799
Just before it reached the bottom...

1222
01:45:24,959 --> 01:45:26,358
...it transformed...

1223
01:45:27,679 --> 01:45:29,431
...into a wee fish.

1224
01:45:31,040 --> 01:45:33,076
It was beautiful magic.

1225
01:45:34,040 --> 01:45:36,190
Wondrous to behold.

1226
01:45:38,719 --> 01:45:41,358
The flower petal had come from a lily.

1227
01:45:43,640 --> 01:45:44,629
Your mother.

1228
01:45:46,600 --> 01:45:48,989
The day I came downstairs...

1229
01:45:49,920 --> 01:45:52,115
...the day the bowl was empty...

1230
01:45:53,599 --> 01:45:55,669
...was the day your mother....

1231
01:45:59,519 --> 01:46:01,430
I know why you're here.

1232
01:46:04,319 --> 01:46:06,230
But I can't help you.

1233
01:46:07,960 --> 01:46:09,598
It would ruin me.

1234
01:46:13,160 --> 01:46:15,515
Do you know why I survived. professor?

1235
01:46:16,040 --> 01:46:17,792
The night I got this?

1236
01:46:19,480 --> 01:46:21,038
Because of her.

1237
01:46:21,920 --> 01:46:23,638
Because she sacrificed herself.

1238
01:46:24,040 --> 01:46:26,315
Because she refused to step aside.

1239
01:46:26,479 --> 01:46:29,551
Because her love was more powerful
than Voldemort.

1240
01:46:29,719 --> 01:46:33,268
-Don't say his name.
-|'m not afraid of the name. professor.

1241
01:46:34,080 --> 01:46:36,116
I'm going to tell you something.

1242
01:46:37,000 --> 01:46:39,833
Something others have only guessed at.

1243
01:46:41,719 --> 01:46:43,152
It's true.

1244
01:46:43,720 --> 01:46:44,948
I am the Chosen One.

1245
01:46:45,920 --> 01:46:48,036
Only I can destroy him.
but in order to do so...

1246
01:46:48,199 --> 01:46:51,350
...I need to know what Tom Riddle
asked you years ago in your office...

1247
01:46:51,520 --> 01:46:53,795
...and I need to know what you told him.

1248
01:46:54,480 --> 01:46:56,789
Be brave. professor.

1249
01:46:58,360 --> 01:47:00,351
Be brave like my mother.

1250
01:47:01,600 --> 01:47:04,160
Otherwise. you disgrace her.

1251
01:47:05,239 --> 01:47:07,434
Otherwise. she died for nothing.

1252
01:47:08,399 --> 01:47:13,393
Otherwise. the bowl
will remain empty forever.

1253
01:47:23,519 --> 01:47:26,511
Please. don't think badly of me
when you see it.

1254
01:47:28,439 --> 01:47:31,590
You've no idea what he was like.
even then.

1255
01:48:06,839 --> 01:48:09,433
RIDDLE:
I was in the library the other night...

1256
01:48:09,600 --> 01:48:11,670
...in the Restricted Section...

1257
01:48:12,520 --> 01:48:15,990
...and I read something rather odd
about a bit of rare magic.

1258
01:48:17,239 --> 01:48:19,878
It's called. as I understand it...

1259
01:48:21,119 --> 01:48:22,393
...a Horcrux.

1260
01:48:24,159 --> 01:48:26,798
-I beg your pardon?
-Horcrux.

1261
01:48:27,199 --> 01:48:29,759
I came across the term while reading...

1262
01:48:29,920 --> 01:48:32,798
...and I didn't fully understand it.

1263
01:48:32,960 --> 01:48:34,632
I'm not sure what you
were reading. Tom...

1264
01:48:34,799 --> 01:48:37,267
...but this is very dark stuff.
very dark indeed.

1265
01:48:37,439 --> 01:48:38,918
Which is...

1266
01:48:39,999 --> 01:48:41,751
...why I came to you.

1267
01:48:44,480 --> 01:48:49,873
A Horcrux is an object in which a person
has concealed part of their soul.

1268
01:48:50,039 --> 01:48:52,553
But I don't understand
how that works. sir.

1269
01:48:55,039 --> 01:48:58,873
One splits one's soul and hides
part of it in an object.

1270
01:48:59,039 --> 01:49:02,509
By doing so. you're protected. should
you be attacked and your body destroyed.

1271
01:49:02,680 --> 01:49:03,749
Protected?

1272
01:49:03,919 --> 01:49:06,991
That part of your soul
that is hidden lives on.

1273
01:49:08,400 --> 01:49:10,709
In other words. you cannot die.

1274
01:49:17,600 --> 01:49:20,637
And how does one split his soul. sir?

1275
01:49:20,800 --> 01:49:23,473
SLUGHORN: I think you already know
the answer to that. Tom.

1276
01:49:24,639 --> 01:49:26,072
Murder.

1277
01:49:26,560 --> 01:49:27,834
Yes.

1278
01:49:28,360 --> 01:49:33,070
Killing rips the soul apart.
It is a violation against nature.

1279
01:49:33,919 --> 01:49:38,470
RIDDLE: Can you only split the soul
once? For instance. isn't seven...?

1280
01:49:38,639 --> 01:49:40,072
Seven?

1281
01:49:40,799 --> 01:49:45,873
Merlin's beard. Tom. Isn't it bad enough
to consider killing one person?

1282
01:49:46,039 --> 01:49:49,634
To rip the soul into seven pieces....

1283
01:49:50,760 --> 01:49:53,672
This is all hypothetical. isn't it. Tom?
All academic?

1284
01:49:58,240 --> 01:49:59,514
Of course. sir.

1285
01:50:02,360 --> 01:50:04,271
It'll be our little secret.

1286
01:50:12,719 --> 01:50:13,913
HARRY:
Sir.

1287
01:50:28,679 --> 01:50:30,715
This is beyond anything I imagined.

1288
01:50:30,879 --> 01:50:33,439
You mean to say he succeeded. sir.
in making a Horcrux?

1289
01:50:33,600 --> 01:50:36,592
Oh. yes. he succeeded. all right.
And not just once.

1290
01:50:36,759 --> 01:50:37,748
What are they exactly?

1291
01:50:37,919 --> 01:50:41,116
Could be anything.
Most commonplace of objects.

1292
01:50:44,159 --> 01:50:45,797
A ring. for example.

1293
01:50:46,399 --> 01:50:47,832
Or a book.

1294
01:50:49,079 --> 01:50:51,354
-Tom Riddle's diary.
-|t's a Horcrux. yes.

1295
01:50:51,839 --> 01:50:53,875
Four years ago. when you saved
Ginny's life...

1296
01:50:54,040 --> 01:50:56,235
...in the Chamber of Secrets.
you brought me this.

1297
01:50:56,399 --> 01:50:58,230
I knew this was
a different kind of magic.

1298
01:50:58,399 --> 01:51:03,189
Very dark. very powerful. But until tonight
I had no idea just how powerful.

1299
01:51:03,360 --> 01:51:05,271
-The ring?
-Be|onged to Voldemort's mother.

1300
01:51:05,639 --> 01:51:10,190
Difficult to find.
Even more difficult to destroy.

1301
01:51:10,360 --> 01:51:14,069
But if you could find them all.
if you did destroy each Horcrux....

1302
01:51:14,239 --> 01:51:15,354
One destroys Voldemort.

1303
01:51:15,520 --> 01:51:18,318
But how would you find them?
They could be hidden anywhere.

1304
01:51:18,479 --> 01:51:21,596
True. But magic. especially dark magic...

1305
01:51:34,999 --> 01:51:36,796
...Ieaves traces.

1306
01:51:44,279 --> 01:51:46,270
It's where you've been going.
isn't it. sir?

1307
01:51:46,439 --> 01:51:48,634
-When you leave the school?
-Yes.

1308
01:51:49,439 --> 01:51:52,397
And I think perhaps
I may have found another.

1309
01:51:52,560 --> 01:51:56,473
But this time.
I cannot hope to destroy it alone.

1310
01:51:57,959 --> 01:52:02,430
Once again.
I must ask too much of you. Harry.

1311
01:52:06,240 --> 01:52:08,435
SNAPE: Have you ever considered
that you ask too much...

1312
01:52:08,600 --> 01:52:11,114
...that you take too much for granted?

1313
01:52:11,280 --> 01:52:16,115
Has it ever crossed your brilliant mind
that I don't want to do this anymore?

1314
01:52:16,280 --> 01:52:18,316
Whether it has or hasn't is irrelevant.

1315
01:52:19,159 --> 01:52:24,711
I will not negotiate with you. Severus.
You agreed. Nothing more to discuss.

1316
01:52:42,360 --> 01:52:43,918
Oh. Harry.

1317
01:52:46,399 --> 01:52:48,629
You need a shave. my friend.

1318
01:52:51,320 --> 01:52:55,359
You know. at times.
I forget how much you've grown.

1319
01:52:55,519 --> 01:52:59,307
At times. I still see the small boy
from the cupboard.

1320
01:53:00,800 --> 01:53:03,075
Forgive my mawkishness. Harry.

1321
01:53:03,520 --> 01:53:04,953
I'm an old man.

1322
01:53:05,119 --> 01:53:06,711
You still look the same to me. sir.

1323
01:53:08,119 --> 01:53:10,997
Just like your mother.
you're unfailingly kind.

1324
01:53:11,159 --> 01:53:14,231
A trait people never fail to undervalue.
I'm afraid.

1325
01:53:16,879 --> 01:53:21,191
The place to which we journey tonight
is extremely dangerous.

1326
01:53:21,360 --> 01:53:24,716
I promised you could accompany me.
and I stand by that promise.

1327
01:53:24,879 --> 01:53:26,631
But there is one condition:

1328
01:53:26,799 --> 01:53:29,871
You must obey every command
I give you. without question.

1329
01:53:30,719 --> 01:53:32,277
Yes. sir.

1330
01:53:32,439 --> 01:53:34,475
You do understand what I'm saying?

1331
01:53:35,040 --> 01:53:37,429
Should I tell you to hide. you hide.

1332
01:53:37,599 --> 01:53:39,829
Should I tell you to run. you run.

1333
01:53:39,999 --> 01:53:43,833
Should I tell you to abandon me
and save yourself. you must do so.

1334
01:53:48,800 --> 01:53:50,313
Your word. Harry.

1335
01:53:51,879 --> 01:53:53,312
My word.

1336
01:53:54,080 --> 01:53:55,672
Take my arm.

1337
01:53:57,039 --> 01:53:59,348
Sir. I thought you couldn't
Apparate within Hogwarts.

1338
01:53:59,999 --> 01:54:03,309
Well. being me has its privileges.

1339
01:54:48,639 --> 01:54:50,197
DUMBLEDORE:
This is the place.

1340
01:54:50,959 --> 01:54:52,472
Oh. yes.

1341
01:54:53,360 --> 01:54:55,828
This place has known magic.

1342
01:55:03,520 --> 01:55:04,999
-Sir!
-In order to gain passage...

1343
01:55:05,159 --> 01:55:06,512
...payment must be made.

1344
01:55:06,680 --> 01:55:10,150
Payment intended
to weaken any intruder.

1345
01:55:11,679 --> 01:55:13,431
-You should've let me. sir.
-No. Harry.

1346
01:55:13,879 --> 01:55:16,473
Your blood's much more precious
than mine.

1347
01:55:37,479 --> 01:55:41,916
Voldemort will not have made it easy
to discover his hiding place.

1348
01:55:42,080 --> 01:55:45,277
He will have put certain defenses
in position.

1349
01:55:47,759 --> 01:55:49,112
Careful.

1350
01:56:11,679 --> 01:56:12,748
There it is.

1351
01:56:14,199 --> 01:56:16,793
The only question is.
how do we get there?

1352
01:56:38,080 --> 01:56:39,832
If you would. Harry.

1353
01:57:25,199 --> 01:57:27,508
Do you think the Horcrux is in there. sir?

1354
01:57:28,119 --> 01:57:29,438
Oh. yes.

1355
01:57:40,080 --> 01:57:41,593
It has to be drunk.

1356
01:57:41,759 --> 01:57:44,478
All of it has to be drunk.

1357
01:57:45,279 --> 01:57:48,476
You remember the conditions on which
I brought you with me?

1358
01:57:48,639 --> 01:57:50,948
This potion might paralyze me.

1359
01:57:51,360 --> 01:57:52,952
Might make me forget why I'm here.

1360
01:57:53,720 --> 01:57:56,871
Might cause me so much pain
that I beg for relief.

1361
01:57:57,119 --> 01:57:58,950
You are not to indulge these requests.

1362
01:57:59,119 --> 01:58:02,509
It's your job. Harry. to make sure
I keep drinking this potion.

1363
01:58:02,679 --> 01:58:05,034
Even if you have to force it
down my throat.

1364
01:58:05,480 --> 01:58:07,516
-Understood?
-Why can't I drink it. sir?

1365
01:58:07,679 --> 01:58:12,878
Because I am much older. much cleverer.
and much less valuable.

1366
01:58:16,639 --> 01:58:18,630
Your good health. Harry.

1367
01:58:34,119 --> 01:58:35,347
Professor.

1368
01:58:37,399 --> 01:58:38,548
Professor!

1369
01:58:38,720 --> 01:58:40,358
[DUMBLEDORE GROANING]

1370
01:58:44,959 --> 01:58:46,392
Harry.

1371
01:58:46,559 --> 01:58:48,948
HARRY:
Professor. can you hear me?

1372
01:58:50,200 --> 01:58:51,315
Professor.

1373
01:59:06,119 --> 01:59:07,188
No. Don't.

1374
01:59:07,360 --> 01:59:09,590
You have to keep drinking.
like you said. Remember?

1375
01:59:18,480 --> 01:59:20,277
DUMBLEDORE: Stop.
-It will stop. It will stop...

1376
01:59:20,439 --> 01:59:24,671
-...but only if you keep drinking.
-P|ease. don't make me.

1377
01:59:24,840 --> 01:59:26,876
-|'m sorry. sir.
-P|ease.

1378
01:59:27,039 --> 01:59:29,234
-Kill me. Kill me!
-No!

1379
01:59:31,080 --> 01:59:32,115
DUMBLEDORE:
It's my fault.

1380
01:59:33,720 --> 01:59:34,869
It's all my fault.

1381
01:59:36,639 --> 01:59:38,197
It's my fault.

1382
01:59:38,360 --> 01:59:41,591
HARRY: Just one more. sir.
One more. and then I promise...

1383
01:59:42,239 --> 01:59:44,469
...I promise I'll do what you say.

1384
01:59:44,639 --> 01:59:46,391
-I promise.
-No.

1385
01:59:47,399 --> 01:59:48,718
Please.

1386
02:00:11,879 --> 02:00:13,278
Harry.

1387
02:00:20,119 --> 02:00:21,108
Water.

1388
02:00:22,080 --> 02:00:23,149
Water.

1389
02:00:23,320 --> 02:00:25,038
Water.

1390
02:00:31,280 --> 02:00:32,998
You did it. sir.

1391
02:00:33,159 --> 02:00:34,558
Look.

1392
02:00:36,480 --> 02:00:37,674
Harry.

1393
02:00:38,999 --> 02:00:40,273
Water.

1394
02:00:41,959 --> 02:00:43,551
A guamen ti.

1395
02:00:43,759 --> 02:00:45,158
DUMBLEDORE:
Water.

1396
02:01:19,839 --> 02:01:21,158
l.umos.

1397
02:01:42,039 --> 02:01:44,314
[SPLASHING]

1398
02:01:48,440 --> 02:01:50,271
l.umos Maximal

1399
02:01:59,360 --> 02:02:01,112
DUMBLEDORE:
Harry.

1400
02:02:04,999 --> 02:02:06,068
Sectumsempra!

1401
02:02:06,239 --> 02:02:07,354
Harry.

1402
02:02:08,280 --> 02:02:09,838
-Stupefy!
DUMBLEDORE: Harry.

1403
02:03:06,600 --> 02:03:07,828
DUMBLEDORE:
Harry.

1404
02:03:11,679 --> 02:03:13,909
Partis Temporus!

1405
02:03:43,919 --> 02:03:46,069
[THUNDER CRASHING]

1406
02:03:54,719 --> 02:03:57,711
Go to your houses. No dawdling.

1407
02:04:13,680 --> 02:04:15,989
[TICKING]

1408
02:04:36,879 --> 02:04:40,428
We need to get you to the hospital
wing. sir. to Madam Pomfrey.

1409
02:04:42,759 --> 02:04:44,078
No.

1410
02:04:45,079 --> 02:04:47,639
Severus. Severus is who I need.

1411
02:04:47,799 --> 02:04:51,189
Wake him. Tell him what happened.

1412
02:04:51,360 --> 02:04:52,952
Speak to no one else.

1413
02:04:53,559 --> 02:04:55,675
Severus. Harry.

1414
02:04:57,479 --> 02:05:00,118
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1415
02:05:00,759 --> 02:05:03,068
Hide yourself below. Harry.

1416
02:05:04,480 --> 02:05:07,358
Don't speak or be seen by anybody
without my permission.

1417
02:05:07,520 --> 02:05:11,149
Whatever happens.
it's imperative you stay below.

1418
02:05:11,920 --> 02:05:13,512
Harry. do as I say.

1419
02:05:13,680 --> 02:05:15,591
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1420
02:05:16,999 --> 02:05:18,227
Trust me.

1421
02:05:19,919 --> 02:05:21,318
Trust me.

1422
02:05:41,040 --> 02:05:42,792
Good evening. Draco.

1423
02:05:43,639 --> 02:05:47,029
What brings you here
on this fine spring evening?

1424
02:05:47,200 --> 02:05:48,872
Who else is here? I heard you talking.

1425
02:05:49,039 --> 02:05:52,952
DUMBLEDORE: I often talk aloud to
myself. I find it extraordinarily useful.

1426
02:05:54,999 --> 02:05:57,718
Have you been whispering
to yourself. Draco?

1427
02:06:00,120 --> 02:06:01,519
Draco...

1428
02:06:02,159 --> 02:06:04,992
-...you are no assassin.
-How do you know what I am?

1429
02:06:05,160 --> 02:06:06,878
I've done things that would shock you.

1430
02:06:07,039 --> 02:06:10,998
Like cursing Katie Bell and hoping that in
return she'd bear a cursed necklace to me?

1431
02:06:11,160 --> 02:06:13,674
Replacing a bottle of mead
with one laced with poison?

1432
02:06:13,840 --> 02:06:15,353
Forgive me. Draco.

1433
02:06:15,520 --> 02:06:17,909
I cannot help feeling these actions
are so weak...

1434
02:06:18,080 --> 02:06:20,355
...your heart can't really
have been in them.

1435
02:06:20,519 --> 02:06:23,591
He trusts me. I was chosen.

1436
02:06:27,239 --> 02:06:28,957
DUMBLEDORE:
Then I shall make it easy for you.

1437
02:06:29,120 --> 02:06:30,712
Exp elliarm us!

1438
02:06:33,920 --> 02:06:36,150
DUMBLEDORE:
Very good. Very good.

1439
02:06:36,320 --> 02:06:37,673
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1440
02:06:37,840 --> 02:06:39,239
You're not alone.

1441
02:06:40,279 --> 02:06:41,268
There are others.

1442
02:06:43,239 --> 02:06:44,592
How?

1443
02:06:45,840 --> 02:06:48,400
The vanishing cabinet
in the Room of Requirement.

1444
02:06:49,119 --> 02:06:51,394
-|'ve been mending it.
DUMBLEDORE: Let me guess.

1445
02:06:51,560 --> 02:06:54,393
It has a sister. A twin.

1446
02:06:54,560 --> 02:06:56,676
In Borgin and Burkes.
They form a passage.

1447
02:06:56,839 --> 02:06:58,557
DUMBLEDORE:
Ingenious.

1448
02:06:59,200 --> 02:07:00,394
Draco...

1449
02:07:00,560 --> 02:07:06,396
...years ago. I knew a boy
who made all the wrong choices.

1450
02:07:07,280 --> 02:07:10,078
-P|ease let me help you.
-I don't want your help!

1451
02:07:10,840 --> 02:07:14,196
Don't you understand? I have to do this.

1452
02:07:15,360 --> 02:07:16,952
I have to kill you.

1453
02:07:17,559 --> 02:07:19,515
Or he's gonna kill me.

1454
02:07:28,639 --> 02:07:32,109
Well. look what we have here.

1455
02:07:33,920 --> 02:07:35,990
Well done. Draco.

1456
02:07:39,520 --> 02:07:41,272
DUMBLEDORE:
Good evening. Bellatrix.

1457
02:07:42,280 --> 02:07:44,350
I think introductions
are in order. don't you?

1458
02:07:44,519 --> 02:07:49,434
BELLATRIX: Love to. Albus. but I'm afraid
we're all on a bit of a tight schedule.

1459
02:07:50,039 --> 02:07:51,358
Do it.

1460
02:07:52,599 --> 02:07:56,558
GREYBACK: He doesn't have the stomach.
just like his father.

1461
02:07:56,960 --> 02:07:58,393
Let me finish him in my own way.

1462
02:07:58,560 --> 02:08:02,030
BELLATRIX: No! The Dark Lord was clear.
the boy is to do it.

1463
02:08:02,199 --> 02:08:04,155
This is your moment. Do it.

1464
02:08:05,639 --> 02:08:07,550
Go on. Draco.

1465
02:08:07,719 --> 02:08:09,789
Now!

1466
02:08:10,999 --> 02:08:12,273
SNAPE:
No.

1467
02:08:23,679 --> 02:08:25,158
DUMBLEDORE:
Severus.

1468
02:08:33,799 --> 02:08:35,198
Please.

1469
02:08:36,160 --> 02:08:37,434
Avada Kedavra.

1470
02:08:52,800 --> 02:08:54,756
[YELLS]

1471
02:09:18,639 --> 02:09:21,756
Yeah!

1472
02:09:39,200 --> 02:09:42,510
BELLATRIX:
Hagrid! Hello?

1473
02:09:42,680 --> 02:09:46,559
HARRY:
Snape! He trusted you!

1474
02:09:49,399 --> 02:09:50,548
[SOUEALING]

1475
02:09:50,719 --> 02:09:52,277
SNAPE:
Go on.

1476
02:09:52,920 --> 02:09:54,558
Incarcerous.

1477
02:09:54,720 --> 02:09:57,280
Fight back! You coward. fight back!

1478
02:09:58,839 --> 02:10:01,911
SNAPE:
No! He belongs to the Dark Lord.

1479
02:10:21,239 --> 02:10:22,558
Sectumsempra!

1480
02:10:30,680 --> 02:10:35,708
You dare use my own spells
against me. Potter?

1481
02:10:36,439 --> 02:10:37,554
Yes.

1482
02:10:38,240 --> 02:10:42,233
I'm the Half-Blood Prince.

1483
02:13:10,039 --> 02:13:13,998
[SOBBING]

1484
02:14:20,960 --> 02:14:22,359
McGONAGALL:
Potter...

1485
02:14:23,040 --> 02:14:25,429
...in light of what has happened...

1486
02:14:26,800 --> 02:14:29,951
...if you should have the need
to talk to someone....

1487
02:14:31,840 --> 02:14:35,674
You should know.
Professor Dumbledore...

1488
02:14:37,440 --> 02:14:39,795
...you meant a great deal to him.

1489
02:14:57,319 --> 02:14:59,389
HERMlONE:
Do you think he would've done it?

1490
02:14:59,559 --> 02:15:01,356
Draco?

1491
02:15:02,400 --> 02:15:03,674
HARRY:
No.

1492
02:15:04,800 --> 02:15:06,756
No. he was lowering his wand.

1493
02:15:07,760 --> 02:15:09,637
In the end. it was Snape.

1494
02:15:10,240 --> 02:15:12,595
It was always Snape.

1495
02:15:12,759 --> 02:15:14,875
And I did nothing.

1496
02:15:21,280 --> 02:15:22,633
It's fake.

1497
02:15:24,160 --> 02:15:25,434
Open it.

1498
02:15:36,000 --> 02:15:39,834
“To the Dark Lord. I know I will be dead
long before you read this...

1499
02:15:40,000 --> 02:15:43,515
...but I want you to know that it was I
who discovered your secret.

1500
02:15:44,480 --> 02:15:48,189
I have stolen the real Horcrux and intend
to destroy it as soon as I can.

1501
02:15:48,360 --> 02:15:51,272
I face death in the hope that
when you meet your match...

1502
02:15:51,439 --> 02:15:53,589
...you will be mortal once more.

1503
02:15:54,839 --> 02:15:56,431
R.A.B.“

1504
02:15:57,640 --> 02:15:59,039
R.A.B.

1505
02:15:59,399 --> 02:16:00,627
Don't know.

1506
02:16:02,560 --> 02:16:05,120
But whoever they are.
they have the real Horcrux.

1507
02:16:06,040 --> 02:16:07,519
Which means it was all a waste.

1508
02:16:08,800 --> 02:16:10,233
All of it.

1509
02:16:16,199 --> 02:16:18,190
Ron's okay with it. you know.

1510
02:16:18,679 --> 02:16:20,112
You and Ginny.

1511
02:16:20,720 --> 02:16:24,269
But if I were you. when he's around.
I'd keep the snogging to a minimum.

1512
02:16:25,559 --> 02:16:27,470
HARRY:
I'm not coming back. Hermione.

1513
02:16:28,599 --> 02:16:31,193
I've got to finish
whatever Dumbledore started.

1514
02:16:31,360 --> 02:16:34,079
And I don't know where that'll lead me...

1515
02:16:34,240 --> 02:16:37,710
...but I'll let you and Ron know
where I am when I can.

1516
02:16:38,999 --> 02:16:41,513
I've always admired your courage. Harry.

1517
02:16:41,679 --> 02:16:44,239
But sometimes. you can be really thick.

1518
02:16:47,160 --> 02:16:49,310
You don't really think
you're going to be able...

1519
02:16:49,479 --> 02:16:51,754
...to find all those Horcruxes
by yourself. do you?

1520
02:16:55,840 --> 02:16:57,432
You need us. Harry.

1521
02:17:12,599 --> 02:17:15,557
HARRY: I never realized
how beautiful this place was.

1522
02:17:17,879 --> 02:17:21,349
[BIRD CRIES]

1523
02:27:08,599 --> 02:27:10,590
[ENGLISH SDH]

